Was thinking about possible follow up pieces and came across the text of the
"emergency" bill we have in the UK to extend the government's powers :
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coronavirus_Act_2020

 

Wondering if the SXSW narrative could be adapted to a "Society's Overton
Window" piece? Something along the lines of govts are always going to
centralise power and times of stress and these changes will be sticky. How
do we avoid a long term move to centralised power? How de mobilise tech to
build and protect our individual spaces to move? Tech has shown it can
support disruption of nations (arab spring) - but how can we use tech to
build cultures, not destroy them.  Tech (at least for the moment) still does
man's bidding - not the other way around, so we need to first start by
telling tech the values and behaviours that we value as a society. That is
essentially impossible at a national level - even at the best of times - and
not when a govt has a centralising mind as now. So we need to get together
in our companies - define our values, measure our culture debt and do all we
can to close our debts - then we need to get together to talk about cross
overs between the values that we value in our workplaces - and allow cross
work metrics to allow individuals to measure themselves against these values
and promote these values in society (because our leaders will not do it for
us)

 

I know - I'm just procrastinating and delaying actually doing my SOC2 work!

 

C


